Fargo.James Holes House:
The James Holes House is a property in Fargo, North Dakota, United States, that was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1987.


== Description and history ==
It was built in 1879 in Italianate style, and was designed and/or built by Pray Brothers. The listing included one contributing building on an area of less than 1 acre (0.40 ha).
